# Dependencies
node_modules/

# Build output
dist/
*.tsbuildinfo
*.tgz

# Sovereign packages: passive permission to commit dist/ if a future workflow
# requires it. Origin/main has no committed dist/ for any of these — rules are
# aspirational only, not enforcement. Current state per mission-70 (2026-05-02)
# investigation:
#   - Hub container build: scripts/local/build-hub.sh does per-package install
#     + npm pack in explicit dep order (storage-provider → repo-event-bridge);
#     does NOT depend on committed dist/.
#   - Local dev cold-start: `npm install` at root FAILS — npm workspaces don't
#     topologically sort prepare-hook execution, so repo-event-bridge's
#     `prepare: tsc` runs before storage-provider's dist/ is reachable. Manual
#     workaround: `cd packages/X && npm install --ignore-scripts && npm run
#     build` per package in dep order, then root `npm install` succeeds.
# Substrate fix tracked: idea-233 (M-Workspace-Install-Bootstrap) — tsc project
# references OR topological-bootstrap script OR build-orchestrator migration.
# Note: prior comments cited "calibration #20" + "until idea-186 lands" — both
# were stale (#20 is an unrelated retired calibration about thread-message
# render; idea-186 npm-workspaces migration shipped via mission-64 PR #122 but
# didn't fix the prepare-hook ordering issue).
!packages/storage-provider/dist/
!packages/storage-provider/dist/**
!packages/repo-event-bridge/dist/
!packages/repo-event-bridge/dist/**
!packages/message-router/dist/
!packages/message-router/dist/**

# Logs
*.log
.ois/

# Mission-47 T3 / Mission-48 — local-fs Hub state directory.
# Default OIS_LOCAL_FS_ROOT for `scripts/local/start-hub.sh` when
# STORAGE_BACKEND=local-fs. Populated by `scripts/state-sync.sh` from
# GCS, or grown organically by Hub during local-fs operation.
local-state/

